knowledge_graph.title: Cannabidiol
knowledge_graph.description: Cannabidiol is a phytocannabinoid, one of 113 identified cannabinoids in Cannabis, along with tetrahydrocannabinol, and accounts for up to 40% of the plant's extract. Medically, it is an anticonvulsant used to treat multiple forms of epilepsy.

related_questions.question: What are the side effects of CBD oil?
related_questions.title: AI Overview
list: Drowsiness and Fatigue: CBD can cause sleepiness or a feeling of tiredness.
Gastrointestinal Issues: Diarrhea is a frequent side effect. Some individuals may also experience decreased appetite, nausea, or stomach upset.
Changes in Liver Enzymes: Elevated liver enzymes have been reported, especially with high doses of CBD.
Dry Mouth: This is another common side effect.
Lightheadedness: Some people may experience dizziness or lightheadedness, especially when standing up.
Liver Damage: High doses of CBD, particularly in the prescription form Epidiolex, have been associated with liver damage.

Drug Interactions: CBD can interact with other medications, potentially increasing or decreasing their effects. This is especially important for medications like blood thinners, anti-epileptics, and immunosuppressants.
Changes in Mood: Some individuals may experience agitation, irritability, or changes in mood, including depression or suicidal thoughts.
Allergic Reactions: Severe allergic reactions, such as angioedema, are possible.
Product Quality: CBD products are not FDA-regulated, and the actual content of CBD in a product may vary from what is stated on the label.
Individual Variation: Side effects can vary from person to person, and some individuals may be more sensitive to CBD than others.

Consult a Healthcare Professional: It is crucial to consult with a doctor or other healthcare professional before taking CBD, especially if you have any pre-existing health conditions or are taking other medications.
Stop Use if Side Effects Occur: If you experience any concerning side effects, discontinue use and consult with a healthcare professional.
